review_size_info: Flavour Name: Dark Chocolate Nuts and Sea Salt
Review: These are great bars. I find when I'm training and dieting nuts tend to fill me up quickly and these do a great job. Not too much sugar and great tasting. Calories are low too. This Dark Chocolate with Sea Salt is my favourite. It's not too sweet and the salt just sets everything off. The cheapest way to buy these is use the Amazon subscription, and also show around .... The price can vary from £1-£2 per bar for the exact same bar. I've only seen the £1 per bar when my local supermarket had buy 1 get 1 free and the bars were £2 which is what a lot of stores charge. On amazon and using subscription you can get then cheaper more often. I really do recommend these for anyone watching their hunger and calories.

review_headline: A very tasty and well-balanced treat
review_size_info: Flavour Name: Dark Chocolate Nuts and Sea Salt
Review: I really like these bars, and so do the other members of my family. It's the slight saltiness and the dark chocolate that work very well together with the nuts.As sweet snacks go, I'd consider it reasonably healthy in moderation, because of the balance of nutrients: 37% fat (mostly good fats), 40% carbs (14% sugar), 18% fibre and 14% protein. It's dairy free and gluten free, and has a very high content of nuts, so contains good micronutrients as well.Overall, if you want to have a filling treat, it's pretty tasty and well-balanced in my opinion.

review_headline: Great size snack for those of us wanting a healthy sugar kick!
review_size_info: Flavour Name: Dark Chocolate Nuts and Sea Salt
Review: I purchased these because I’m on the 16:8 IF diet along with moderate carbs to lower my blood sugars after the shock of finding out I have Diabetes 2. I didn’t want medication as I know diet makes a huge difference, so decided to try there first. Obviously my sweet tooth was going to be my downfall but I found these delicious nut bars and oh my word, wish I’d found them years ago! They’re only 16g carbs (I’m on 140-150) and so give me the sweet treat I need to stay on plan. They’re lovely, slightly chewy and the salt kick after each bite makes these very moreish. Highly recommended and can’t wait try more of the range.

review_headline: Possibly the best tasting healthiest snack bar you can buy?
review_size_info: Flavour Name: Dark Chocolate Almond Mint
Review: Not a protein bar but a very health-designed snack bar, and true to their advertising claims, both genuinely good for you and tastes fantastic. If you've tried the other flavours in the series, all of which are imaginative, this one is outstanding.I've attached the ingredients list from the box as I think it is slightly clearer than on the webpage at the time of writing and worth analyzing to your heart's content.I bought a few boxes at the old price but it felt a bit like a luxury item: at the new price, a little over £1 a bar, they are fantastic value in my opinion. At this price,m they'll probably keep me as a customer.

review_headline: Another Good Kind Bar, for me its not a great kind bar.
review_size_info: Flavour Name: Caramel Almond and Sea Salt
Review: The Kind Caramel Almon and Sea salt bars are the third variety I have tried; and the first that didn't bowl me over. Kind bars are generally quite good for your; their sales pitch is ingredients you can see. In this case the bar is mostly almonds held together by caramel. As a result The 40g bar is 7.3g of Fibre, ~6g of protein and ~5g of sugar so the energy from the bar lasts. Between the caramel and almonds you are accounting for 81% of the weight of the bar. I don't want to comment if this is healthy for you or not its 203cal in 40g. The nuts high protein do make you feel fuller for longer.The taste is excellent with the caramel and almonds really working nicely together. Unlike the Kind Bar, Dark Chocolate / Nuts & Sea Salt the salt was much more subtle; adding to the overall experience rather than being a significant flavor.The flavor is nice (the apple one was nicest to my tastebuds but has most sugar) and compared to my previous kind bars this is the healthiest; I just don't enjoy the texture of a bar that is basically pure almond with some flavor. Its very crunchy and its not quite right for me.

review_size_info: Flavour Name: Dark Chocolate Nuts and Sea Salt
Review: Had to search high and low for ingredients, eventually found them under the fold of the wrapper - Contains palm oil so won't be buying again.What really bothers me about this product is the name and the branding and the fact that they then go and use a product which is not kind in any way what so ever.
